            <thetext>qooxdoo 0.7 does not support the following text-formatting properties: transform, lineHeight, letterSpacing, wordSpacing.

In SWT there is a RichText widget which support such properties. Maybe the qooxdoo implementation could be named RichLabel.

If these properties should be themeable, too, these need to be a API outside the font thememing to handle them.

Until then Labels could use these styles by wrapping all content into HTML and applying them to the outer DIV/SPAN element. For textareas, which don&#39;t need any preferred size calculation, one can simply apply these properties using setStyleProperty.</thetext>
